New Records: De'Aaron Fox's 109 points are the most over a two-game span in Sacramento Kings franchise history, passing DeMarcus Cousins.
Key Match Events: De'Aaron Fox scored 49 points to lead the Sacramento Kings to a 121-117 victory over the Utah Jazz.
Fox went 16 of 30 from the field and made 14 of 19 from the free-throw line, adding nine assists and two steals.
The Kings trailed 89-78 in the third quarter but took a 118-116 lead on a Jordan McLaughlin 3-pointer with 1:04 remaining.
Both teams shot nearly the same percentage from 3-point range, with the Kings making 19 of 41 shots (46.3%) and the Jazz making 12 of 26 shots (46.2%).
Miscellaneous Highlights: De'Aaron Fox made his first seven shots from the floor, including three 3-pointers in the first quarter, and had 26 points by halftime.
The Jazz had five players score at least 16 points in a game for the first time this season.
